Author::::pitselehprintsesin
DateTime::::2016-03-11T19:12:03Z
Have a slow clap for your completely misunderstanding nature of depression. People diagnosed with clinical depression often have the endogenous (rather than reactive) kind; that is to say, they are not depressed 'about' anything in particular. They simply feel low and/or disengaged (among other things) most of the time without direct cause. Of course, as harrowperson mentioned, there are plenty of things a child can be reactively depressed about. But I'm afraid you don't have any idea what you're talking about if you think (as your comment suggests) that depression always follows from an unhappy experience.



